Brand Positioning Core

Positioning is how your brand is perceived in the mind of your audience.
StorySell positions brands through narrative, clarity, and emotional differentiation.

## 1. Positioning Components

Category – The market you choose to play in

Audience – Who you are for

Unique Perspective – Your worldview

Promise – What you guarantee

Reasons to Believe – Proof

Emotional Outcome – What people gain emotionally

Competitive Edge – How you stand out

## 2. Story-Based Positioning Statement

Use this template:

For [target audience],
who [needs / struggles / desires],
our brand [brand name]
is the only [category & differentiator]
that [unique promise],
because [founder truth + evidence].

## 3. Positioning Map

Plot your brand using:

Price

Emotion

Functionality

Story depth

Founder role

Category maturity

Strong brands own a quadrant clearly and intentionally.
